Only cargo food trucks are allowed to move “in order to protect the food chain in Nairobi”.
All tuk tuk and matatu drivers have been ordered to wear masks going forward. “We have begun local production of the face masks & PPE’s. Masks will be distributed through counties and association chairpersons,” CS Kagwe said.
